  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C (400\u00b0F). Spread the chickpeas on a baking sheet and roast for 10\u201312 minutes until golden, stirring halfway through.",
    "While the chickpeas roast, combine the cannellini beans, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, parsley, and dill in a large bowl.",
    "Add the roasted chickpeas to the vegetable mixture.",
    "Whisk together the lemon juice, zest, olive oil, sumac, salt, and pepper to make the dressing.",
    "Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently until everything is evenly coated.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary, adding more salt or sumac for extra bitterness.",
    "Serve immediately or chill for 10 minutes to let flavors meld."
